-- Novelis in Talks to Buy Bp’s 60% Stake in Logan, Mint Says
-- B y   A n i l   V a r m a
-- 2010-10-07T01:46:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/novelis-in-talks-to-buy-bp-s-60-holding-in-logan-venture-mint-reports.html
Novelis Inc., the U.S.-based aluminum
unit of India’s Hindalco Industries Ltd., is in discussions to
buy the 60 percent stake BP Plc holds in the joint venture Logan
Aluminum Inc., the Mint reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Novelis may purchase shares of U.S.-based Logan for $600
million, the newspaper said. BP owns Logan shares through a
wholly-owned unit ARCO Aluminum Inc., according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anil Varma in Mumbai at 
